This paper focuses on interpretability of deep learning models, specifically Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) with gated mechanisms. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), or systems and control (cs.SD). However, given the focus on text classification tasks and the use of Finite State Automaton (FSA) for processing sequential data, it is most likely that the paper belongs to the natural language processing (cs.CL) category. The other categories are still possible but less likely based on the information provided in the abstract.
